<subSubSection pageId="257" pageNumber="258" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="257.[151,1437,1374,1905]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[269,517,1554,1581]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="254 - 267" refId="ref367602" refString="Rondani, C. (1845 f) Sulle specie italiane del genere Merodon. Memoria decimaquarta per servire alla ditterologia italiana. Nuovi Annali delle Scienze Naturali e Rendiconto delle Sessioni della Societa Agraria e dell'Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna, Series 2, 4, 254 - 267." type="journal article" year="1845">Rondani (1845f: 256)</bibRefCitation>
considered the males of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1805)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[809,1213,1554,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narcissi">
<emphasis box="[809,1008,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon narcissi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[1025,1204,1554,1581]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="15 - 372" refId="ref350302" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1805) Systema antliatorum secundum ordines, genera, species adiectis synonymis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. C. Reichard, Brunsvigae [= Brunswick], xiv + 15 - 372 + 30 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 15806" type="book chapter" year="1805">Fabricius, 1805</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and the females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann, 1822" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1822" box="[199,629,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constans">
<emphasis box="[199,410,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon constans</emphasis>
Wiedemann, 1822
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1805)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[692,1142,1590,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis box="[692,933,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon ferrugineus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[952,1133,1590,1617]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="15 - 372" refId="ref350302" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1805) Systema antliatorum secundum ordines, genera, species adiectis synonymis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. C. Reichard, Brunsvigae [= Brunswick], xiv + 15 - 372 + 30 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 15806" type="book chapter" year="1805">Fabricius, 1805</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as the same species but, instead of applying the Principle of Priority, he incorrectly proposed the substitute name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[1182,1429,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[1182,1429,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[199,451,1662,1689]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="193 - 231" refId="ref369428" refString="Rondani, C. (1865 c) Diptera italica non vel minus cognita descripta vel annotata observationibus nonnullis additis. Fasc. II. Muscidae. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 8, 193 - 231." type="journal article" year="1865">Rondani (1865c: 207)</bibRefCitation>
used 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[523,773,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[523,773,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species and he (
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[1091,1300,1662,1690]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani 1857: 61</bibRefCitation>
) reaffirmed having proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[388,634,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[388,634,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to combine 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[767,962,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narcissi">
<emphasis box="[767,962,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon narcissi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1822" box="[973,1178,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constans">
<emphasis box="[973,1178,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon constans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1794)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicans">
<emphasis box="[1228,1436,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon flavicans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[207,386,1735,1761]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="5" refId="ref350243" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1794) Entomologia systematica emandata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Vol. 4. C. G. Proft, Hafniae [= Copenhagen], [6] + 472 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1794">Fabricius, 1794</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schiner, I. R." box="[404,620,1735,1761]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="185 - 368" refId="ref372447" refString="Schiner, I. R. (1860) Fauna Austriaca. Die Fliegen (Diptera). Nach der analytischen Methode bearbeitet, mit der Characteristik sammtlicher europaischer Gattungen, der Beschreibung aller in Deutschland vorkommenden Arten und der Aufzahlung aller bisher beschriebene europaischen Arten. I. Theil. [Heft 3 / 4]. C. Gerold's Sohn, Wien, pp. 185 - 368." type="book chapter" year="1860">Schiner (1860: 344</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schiner, I. R." box="[630,744,1735,1761]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" refId="ref372905" refString="Schiner, I. R. (1864) Catalogus systematicus Dipterorum Europae. Societatis Zoologico-Botanicae, Vindobonae [= Wien], 115 pp." type="book" year="1864">1864: 108</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M. &amp; Stein, P." box="[764,1057,1735,1761]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="1 - 747" refId="ref346041" refString="Bezzi, M. &amp; Stein, P. (1907) Cyclorrapha Aschiza. Cyclorrapha Schizophora: Schizometopa. In: Becker, T., Bezzi, M., Kertesz, K. &amp; Stein, P. (Eds.), Katalog der palaarktischen Dipteren. Band III. G. Wesselenyi in Hodmezovasarhely, Budapest, pp. 1 - 747." type="book chapter" year="1907">Bezzi &amp; Stein (1907: 121)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kertesz, K." box="[1068,1292,1735,1761]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" refId="ref355436" refString="Kertesz, K. (1910) Catalogus Dipterorum hucusque descriptorum. Volumen VII. Syrphidae, Dorylaidae, Phoridae, Clythiidae. Museum Nationale Hungaricum, Budapestini [= Budapest], 470 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5147" type="book" year="1910">Kertész (1910: 280)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sack, P." pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="289 - 336" refId="ref372196" refString="Sack, P. (1931) 31. Syrphidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region. Band IV / 6. Lieferung 59. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 289 - 336." type="book chapter" year="1931">Sack (1931: 314)</bibRefCitation>
placed it in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1794)" authorityName="Peck" authorityYear="1988" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[569,979,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equestris">
<emphasis box="[569,779,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon equestris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[793,970,1771,1797]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="5" refId="ref350243" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1794) Entomologia systematica emandata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Vol. 4. C. G. Proft, Hafniae [= Copenhagen], [6] + 472 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1794">Fabricius, 1794</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
while 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[1055,1257,1771,1797]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" pagination="275 - 353" refId="ref345779" refString="Bezzi, M. (1894) I ditteri del Trentino. Saggio di un elenco delle specie di ditteri finora osservate nel Trentino [concl.]. Atti della Societa Veneto - Trentina di Scienze Naturali Residente in Padova, Series 2, 1, 275 - 353." type="journal article" year="1894">Bezzi (1894: 283)</bibRefCitation>
considered it to be a valid species. The 
<typeStatus box="[456,504,1807,1833]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">type</typeStatus>
material for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[647,894,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[647,894,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be the same as for the name it was proposed to replace, i. e., 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[395,595,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narcissi">
<emphasis box="[395,595,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon narcissi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is no 
<typeStatus box="[758,806,1843,1869]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[852,1053,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narcissi">
<emphasis box="[852,1053,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="257" pageNumber="258">Merodon narcissi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the ZMUC where Fabricius’s collection is preserved (
<bibRefCitation author="Michelsen, V." box="[466,652,1879,1905]" pageId="257" pageNumber="258" refId="ref359952" refString="Michelsen, V. (2017) List of Fabricius types in the Diptera collection of the Natural History Museum of Denmark, University of Copenhagen. Available from: https: // samlinger. snm. ku. dk / toer-og-vaadsamlinger / zoologi / entomologi / diptera-collection / diptera _ fabriciustypes _ pdf. pdf (accessed 08 September 2020)" type="book" year="2017">Michelsen 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
